{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"e28e4b48-36ef-4b96-b9f2-49b16c7f54ec","content":"With xUnit v3 + MTP, the VSTest filter syntax changes. Here's the translation:\n\n**Old (VSTest/xUnit v2):**\n```\ndotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests&Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\n**New (MTP/xUnit v3):**\n```\ndotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests&trait=Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\nKey differences in MTP filter syntax:\n- **Traits** use the format `trait=Name=Value` instead of just `Name=Value`\n- Operators (`~` for contains, `&` for AND) remain the same\n\nAlternatively, you can run the MTP executable directly:\n```\ndotnet run -- --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests&trait=Category=Smoke\"\n```","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"8c2dc16e-4e05-4fd3-acbe-219bae5bb0d3","outputTokens":208,"requestId":"8430:252037:1E475E5:219DDE7:6A0ACF30"},"id":"6b22f4b3-a7a0-42e4-92e8-c1e665de48c2","timestamp":"2026-05-18T08:35:02.510Z","parentId":"3460fb14-bfb3-45c8-bc3c-9f620fa8b660"}
